              teachingCode: '# Train the model\nhistory = model.fit(\n    X_train, y_train,\n    epochs=50,\n    batch_size=32,\n    validation_split=0.2\n)\n\n# Access training history\nhistory.history["loss"]       # training loss per epoch\nhistory.history["val_loss"]   # validation loss per epoch\nhistory.history["accuracy"]   # training accuracy\nhistory.history["val_accuracy"]  # validation accuracy\n\n# If val_loss increases while loss decreases → overfitting',
              question: 'During training, validation loss decreases for 10 epochs then starts increasing while training loss continues decreasing. What is happening?',
              code: 'history = model.fit(X_train, y_train, epochs=50, validation_split=0.2)',
