              teaching: 'Dropout layers randomly set a fraction of neurons to zero during training, forcing the network to learn redundant representations. The rate parameter (e.g., 0.3) means 30% of neurons are dropped each training step. This is one of the most effective regularization techniques for preventing overfitting, especially important in genomics where datasets are often small.',
              teachingCode: 'from tensorflow.keras import layers\n\n# Add Dropout between Dense layers\nmodel = keras.Sequential([\n    layers.Dense(128, activation="relu", input_shape=(100,)),\n    layers.Dropout(0.3),  # drop 30% of neurons\n    layers.Dense(64, activation="relu"),\n    layers.Dropout(0.3),\n    layers.Dense(1, activation="sigmoid")\n])\n\n# Dropout is ONLY active during training\n# During prediction, all neurons are used\n# Typical rates: 0.2-0.5 for hidden layers',
              question: 'Complete the code to add a Dropout layer that drops 30% of neurons:',
              code: 'layers.___(0.3)',
