              teachingCode: 'import networkx as nx\n\nG = nx.Graph()\n\n# Add node with attributes\nG.add_node("TP53", gene_type="tumor_suppressor", organism="human")\nG.add_node("MDM2", gene_type="oncogene", organism="human")\n\n# Add edge with attributes\nG.add_edge("TP53", "MDM2", weight=0.95, evidence="yeast2hybrid")\n\n# Access attributes\nG.nodes["TP53"]["gene_type"]      # "tumor_suppressor"\nG.edges["TP53", "MDM2"]["weight"] # 0.95\n\n# Iterate with attributes\nfor node, data in G.nodes(data=True):\n    print(node, data)',
              question: 'Complete the code to access the weight attribute of an edge:',
